            "answer_text": "\"Morality\" refers to a code of conduct, about what actions are considered right and what is wrong. See The Definition of Morality An ideology is a system of beliefs or doctrines that intend to guide social groups or individuals, most often with political or sociological connotations. Ideology and morality are interconnected because most people subscribe to a certain ideology based on their moral convictions, although that is not necessarily true. ",
